Cynthia Morgan’s former Manager, Joy Tongo has released an official statement concerning the controversy sparked up by the artist yesterday about Jude Okoye. According to Joy, Cynthia Morgan left the record label on her own before her contract expired. She also revealed that Cynthia released two songs after she left Jude Okoye without getting any resistance or court injunction from him. READ ALSO:Davido forgives Cynthia Morgan, offers to record song with her Joy added that while with Jude, Cynthia got a Range Rover, money to buy land for her mother and an apartment from Jude. Basically she’s saying that Cynthia left them and failed on her own. in fact, she said Cynthia Morgan lied all along. Read her full statement below.